The '''1978 FIBA World Championship''' was the 8th [[FIBA World Championship]], the international [[basketball]] world championship for men's teams. The tournament was hosted by [[Philippines]] from October 1 to 14, 1978.
[[Rizal Memorial Coliseum]] at [[Manila]] and [[Araneta Coliseum]] at [[Quezon City]] (both cities in [[Metro Manila]]), were the venues for the event.<ref name="GAME DETAILS">{{cite web|last1=Velasco|first1=Santiago|title=VIII World Championship (Manila 1978) Game Details|url=http://www.linguasport.com/baloncesto/internacional/mundial/1978_MANILA_gd.htm|website=LinguaSport.com|accessdate=18 January 2016}}</ref>

==Host selection==
On 11 July 1974 at the FIBA Congress held in [[San Juan, Puerto Rico|San Juan]], [[Puerto Rico]], the Philippines was unanimously chosen as hosts after Argentina and Spain withdrew their bids.<ref>{{cite news|title=Manila Chosen Site Of World Basketball Meet|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=pHJSAAAAIBAJ&sjid=E0cDAAAAIBAJ&pg=5060%2C1197577|accessdate=18 January 2016|publisher=The Virgin Islands Daily News|date=12 July 1974|location=San Juan, Puerto Rico}}</ref>

