{{main|FINA World Junior Synchronised Swimming Championships}}

The '''9th [[FINA]] World Junior Synchronised Swimming Championships''' was held August 15–18, 2002 in [[Montreal, Quebec]], Canada. The synchronised swimmers are aged between 15 and 18 years old, from 31 nations, swimming in four events: Solo, Duet, Team and Free combination.<ref name=Bean>{{cite book | url=https://books.google.com/?id=o-dD3p8eTYUC&lpg=PA227&pg=PA235#v=onepage&q&f=false | title=Synchronized Swimming: An American History | publisher=McFarland | author=Bean, Dawn Pawson | year=2005 | pages=312| isbn=9780786419487 }}</ref>

