{{Infobox football biography | name = Erin Barnett | fullname = Erin Anthony Barnett | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1996|9|2|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Gibraltar]] | height = | currentclub = [[Gibraltar United F.C.|Gibraltar United]] | clubnumber = 5 | position = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]] | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = <!--all match stats are taken from the GFA website's fixtures/results page. There is no single appearances page, so refer to each individual match page--> | years1 = 2013–2015 | clubs1 = [[Lions Gibraltar F.C.|Lions Gibraltar]] | caps1 = 28 | goals1 = 1 | years2 = 2016 | clubs2 = [[Lions Gibraltar F.C.|Lions Gibraltar]] | caps2 = 0 | goals2 = 0 | years3 = 2016– | clubs3 = [[Gibraltar United F.C.|Gibraltar United]] | caps3 = 51 | goals3 = 0 | nationalyears1 = 2013–2014 | nationalteam1 = [[Gibraltar national under-19 football team|Gibraltar U-19]] | nationalcaps1= 7 | nationalgoals1 = 0 | nationalyears2 = 2015– | nationalteam2 = [[Gibraltar national football team|Gibraltar]] | nationalcaps2= 14 | nationalgoals2 = 0 | nationalyears3 = 2017– | nationalteam3 = [[Gibraltar national under-21 football team|Gibraltar U-21]] | nationalcaps3 = 3 | nationalgoals3 = 0 | pcupdate = 27 November 2018 | ntupdate = 19 November 2018 }}
'''Erin Anthony Barnett''' (born 2 September 1996) is a Gibraltarian [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Gibraltar Premier Division]] side [[Lions Gibraltar F.C.|Lions Gibraltar]] and the [[Gibraltar national football team|Gibraltar]] national team. He is mainly a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|centre back]] player.
==Club career== Barnett emerged from the [[Lions Gibraltar F.C.|Lions Gibraltar]] youth set up in 2013, at the age of 16, and quickly became a regular fixture in the side. He was released by the club in 2015, however. After a year without a club, he re-signed in summer 2016. Before the transfer window closed, he moved again as he was signed by [[Gibraltar United F.C.|Gibraltar United]].
==International career==
Barnett was first called up to the [[Gibraltar national football team|Gibraltar senior team]] at the age of 17 in September 2015 for matches against [[Republic of Ireland national football team|Republic of Ireland]] and [[Poland national football team|Poland]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=GFA Official Site |title=Final 23 man Squad announced for European Qualifiers v Ireland & Poland |url=http://www.gibraltarfa.com/media-enquiries/news/01-09-2015/final-23-man-squad-announced-for-european-qualifiers-v-ireland-poland |language= |date=2015-09-04 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150912144441/http://www.gibraltarfa.com/media-enquiries/news/01-09-2015/final-23-man-squad-announced-for-european-qualifiers-v-ireland-poland |archivedate=2015-09-12 |df= }}</ref> He made his international début with Gibraltar on 4 September 2015 in game with [[Republic of Ireland national football team|Republic of Ireland]].
