{{morefootnotes|date=November 2018}} {{Use dmy dates|date=May 2014}} {{Infobox football tournament | name = Torneo del Oeste | image = | imagesize = | alt = | caption = | organiser = [[Unión de Rugby de Cuyo|URC]] | founded = {{Start date and age|2000}} | abolished = | region = Argentina | number of teams = 10 | qualifier for = | related comps = [[Torneo de la URBA]] | domestic cup = | confed cup = | current champions = Los Tordos <small>(2013)</small> | most successful club = Los Tordos <small>(6 titles)</small> | broadcasters = | motto = | website = | current = | American = }}
The '''Campeonato Anual Regional del Oeste''', commonly known as the '''Torneo Cuyano''' or '''Torneo del Oeste''', is a regional [[rugby union]] competition in [[Argentina]]. The competition started in 2000 and involves 10 clubs from the unions of [[Unión de Rugby de Cuyo|Cuyo]] (Mendoza), San Luis and San Juan [[provinces of Argentina|provinces]].
This annual tournament has traditionally been dominated by ''Mendocino'' clubs. As in other inter-provincial tournaments, such as the [[Torneo del Litoral]] or [[Torneo del Noroeste]], the best placed clubs in the Torneo del Oeste qualify for the [[Torneo del Interior]].
