'''Tour de Leelanau''' was a [[USA Cycling]] [[road bicycle racing]] event held annually from 2005 to 2008 in [[Leelanau County, Michigan]] (near [[Traverse City]]).

Starting in 2007, the men's event is sanctioned by the [[Union Cycliste Internationale]] (UCI) and serves as the last stop on the [[2006-2007 UCI America Tour]] and the [[2007 USA Cycling Professional Tour]].

== Route ==
The Tour de Leelanau is a point-to-point open road race that runs through much of the [[Leelanau Peninsula]] including the villages of [[Leland, Michigan|Leland]], [[Maple City, Michigan|Maple City]], Empire, [[Glen Arbor]], [[Cedar, Michigan|Cedar]], [[Lake Leelanau]], [[Suttons Bay, Michigan|Suttons Bay]], and [[Northport, Michigan|Northport]] before the finish at Leelanau Sands Casino in [[Peshawbestown, Michigan]]. In 2008 the men’s course was 109.5 miles; the women’s course 69.5 miles.

